{
  "id": "fr_a1_lesson_013",
  "language": "fr",
  "level": "A1",
  "title": "La météo et le futur proche",
  "description": "Talk about the weather and near-future plans with \"aller + infinitif\" — the exact grammar used in the weather-forecast audio clips TCF listening loves.",
  "metadata": { "estimatedMinutes": 9, "xpReward": 50 },
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "c1",
      "type": "TextCard",
      "title": "La météo et le futur proche",
      "content": {
        "subtitle": "Module 6 · Leçon 1",
        "body": "Weather talk is small talk everywhere — and weather forecasts are a favorite TCF listening format. They also give us a perfect excuse to learn the near future tense."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Parler de la météo",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "Weather expressions almost always use the impersonal \"il\" (like English \"it's raining\").",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "Il fait beau.", "translation": "The weather is nice." },
          { "text": "Il fait chaud / froid.", "translation": "It's hot / cold." },
          { "text": "Il pleut.", "translation": "It's raining." },
          { "text": "Il neige.", "translation": "It's snowing." }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 40 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Le futur proche : aller + infinitif",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "To talk about the near future, conjugate \"aller\" (to go) and add an infinitive — exactly like English \"going to\".",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "je vais manger", "translation": "I am going to eat" },
          { "text": "tu vas sortir", "translation": "you are going to go out" },
          { "text": "il/elle va pleuvoir", "translation": "it is going to rain" },
          { "text": "nous allons voyager", "translation": "we are going to travel" },
          { "text": "vous allez arriver", "translation": "you are going to arrive" },
          { "text": "ils/elles vont partir", "translation": "they are going to leave" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 45 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c4",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "il va faire beau",
        "nativeTranslation": "il va faire beau",
        "englishTranslation": "the weather is going to be nice",
        "pronunciation": "eel vah fair boh",
        "ipa": "il va fɛʁ bo",
        "partOfSpeech": "expression",
        "difficulty": "medium",
        "exampleSentence": "Demain, il va faire beau avec vingt degrés.",
        "nativeExample": "Tomorrow, the weather will be nice, with twenty degrees.",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/il-va-faire-beau.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5",
      "type": "InfoCard",
      "title": "Le bulletin météo de l'examen",
      "content": {
        "tone": "tip",
        "body": "\"Demain, il va faire beau à Paris avec des températures de vingt degrés. Il va pleuvoir dans le sud.\" — this exact weather-forecast format, using futur proche, is a very common TCF listening clip. Listen for the city and the temperature."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c6",
      "type": "FlashCard",
      "title": "Quick flip",
      "content": { "front": "il va pleuvoir", "back": "it's going to rain", "hint": "Tap to reveal the meaning" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 15 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c7",
      "type": "MultipleChoiceCard",
      "title": "Choisissez la bonne forme",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Nous ___ (voyager) en France l'été prochain.",
        "options": [
          { "id": "a", "text": "allons voyager" },
          { "id": "b", "text": "va voyager" },
          { "id": "c", "text": "vais voyager" },
          { "id": "d", "text": "allez voyager" }
        ]
      },
      "validation": { "correctOptionId": "a" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c8",
      "type": "FillBlankCard",
      "title": "Complétez la phrase",
      "content": {
        "textWithBlanks": "Demain, il ___ faire froid. (is going to)",
        "hint": "Third-person singular of \"aller\""
      },
      "validation": { "acceptedAnswers": ["va"] },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c9",
      "type": "ListeningCard",
      "title": "Écoutez le bulletin météo",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Quel temps va-t-il faire demain à Paris ?",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/meteo-beau-paris.mp3" },
        "options": [
          { "id": "a", "text": "il va pleuvoir" },
          { "id": "b", "text": "il va faire beau" },
          { "id": "c", "text": "il va neiger" }
        ]
      },
      "validation": { "correctOptionId": "b" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 25 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c10",
      "type": "MatchingCard",
      "title": "Associez le pronom au verbe \"aller\"",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Match each subject pronoun to its correct form of \"aller\".",
        "pairs": [
          { "id": "p1", "left": "je", "right": "vais" },
          { "id": "p2", "left": "tu", "right": "vas" },
          { "id": "p3", "left": "nous", "right": "allons" },
          { "id": "p4", "left": "ils", "right": "vont" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 40 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c11",
      "type": "TrueFalseCard",
      "title": "Vrai ou faux ?",
      "content": {
        "statement": "Le futur proche se forme avec \"avoir\" + infinitif."
      },
      "validation": { "answer": false },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 15 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c12",
      "type": "DragOrderCard",
      "title": "Construisez la phrase",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Arrange the words to say \"It's going to rain tomorrow.\"",
        "items": [
          { "id": "w3", "text": "demain." },
          { "id": "w1", "text": "Il va" },
          { "id": "w2", "text": "pleuvoir" }
        ]
      },
      "validation": { "correctOrder": ["w1", "w2", "w3"] },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c13",
      "type": "MultipleSelectCard",
      "title": "Quelles phrases utilisent le futur proche ?",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Select every sentence using the near future (aller + infinitive).",
        "options": [
          { "id": "a", "text": "Je vais manger." },
          { "id": "b", "text": "Je mange." },
          { "id": "c", "text": "Nous allons voyager." },
          { "id": "d", "text": "Ils vont sortir." }
        ]
      },
      "validation": { "correctOptionIds": ["a", "c", "d"] },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c14",
      "type": "ConversationCard",
      "title": "Parler du week-end",
      "content": {
        "scenario": "Entre amis",
        "lines": [
          { "speaker": "Sami", "text": "Qu'est-ce que tu vas faire ce week-end ?", "translation": "What are you going to do this weekend?" },
          { "speaker": "Ana", "text": "Je vais visiter Paris, s'il fait beau.", "translation": "I'm going to visit Paris, if the weather is nice." },
          { "speaker": "Sami", "text": "La météo annonce du soleil, alors !", "translation": "The forecast says sun, so that's good!" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 45 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c15",
      "type": "SpeakingCard",
      "title": "À vous de parler",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Repeat this weekend plan out loud.",
        "targetText": "Ce week-end, je vais visiter Paris, s'il fait beau.",
        "referenceAudio": { "key": "fr/a1/plan-week-end.mp3" }
      },
      "validation": { "placeholderScore": true },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c16",
      "type": "QuizCard",
      "title": "Mini contrôle",
      "content": {
        "intro": "Two quick questions before the summary.",
        "questions": [
          {
            "id": "q1",
            "kind": "mc",
            "prompt": "Comment forme-t-on le futur proche ?",
            "options": [
              { "id": "a", "text": "être + infinitif" },
              { "id": "b", "text": "aller (conjugué) + infinitif" },
              { "id": "c", "text": "avoir + participe passé" }
            ]
          },
          { "id": "q2", "kind": "tf", "prompt": "\"Il neige\" veut dire \"it's snowing\"." }
        ]
      },
      "validation": { "answers": { "q1": "b", "q2": true } },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 40 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c17",
      "type": "SummaryCard",
      "title": "Ce que vous avez appris",
      "content": {
        "heading": "Key takeaways",
        "points": [
          "Weather expressions: il fait beau/chaud/froid, il pleut, il neige",
          "Futur proche: aller (conjugated) + infinitive, for near-future plans",
          "Weather forecasts are a classic TCF listening format — listen for city + temperature",
          "\"Qu'est-ce que tu vas faire...?\" is a natural way to ask about plans"
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
